# EyeCare

Free desktop eye protection app that reduces eye strain by filtering blue light and controlling screen brightness. Built with Electron, React, TypeScript, Vite, and Tailwind CSS v4.

## Features

- Blue-light filter overlay (warmth and brightness controls)
- Day/Night toggle (light/dark UI theme + filter presets)
- Presets (Health, Office, Reading, Game, Movie, Editing, Custom)
- Global keyboard shortcuts
- Clean UI styled with Tailwind CSS v4
- Cross-platform packaging via Electron Forge

## Screenshots

- Add screenshots (PNG/JPG) under `docs/screenshots/` and reference them here:
  - Display Settings
  - Night Mode
  - Presets

## Getting Started

### Prerequisites

- Node.js 18+ (LTS recommended)
- npm 9+

### Install

```bash
npm install
```

### Development

```bash
npm run dev
```

- This starts the Vite dev server and launches Electron.
- Preview is available at the printed localhost URL (e.g., http://localhost:5174/).

### Lint

```bash
npm run lint
```

### Package (build installers)

```bash
npm run make
```

- Output is created under `out/` (e.g., Windows Squirrel installer).

## Keyboard Shortcuts

- Ctrl + Alt + F — Toggle filter overlay
- Ctrl + Alt + D — Open Display page
- Ctrl + Alt + S — Open Settings page

## Day/Night Mode

- Day: Light UI + filter preset (warmer off, full brightness)
- Night: Dark UI + filter preset (warmer on, reduced brightness)

The UI theme switches using Tailwind’s `dark` class on `<html>`, and cards/layout use `dark:` variants.

## Tech Stack

- Electron Forge + Vite
- React + TypeScript
- Tailwind CSS v4 (PostCSS integration)


## Project Structure (key files)

- `src/pages/Dashboard.tsx` — main UI with sliders, presets, Day/Night
- `src/pages/settings.tsx` — settings page (keyboard shortcuts shown)
- `src/pages/schedule.tsx` — schedule UI
- `src/main.ts` — Electron main process (overlay, global shortcuts, IPC)
- `src/preload.ts` — safe IPC bridge
- `src/router.tsx` — app routing and sidebar
- `src/index.css` — Tailwind directives + custom styles
- `postcss.config.cjs` — Tailwind v4 PostCSS plugin

## Troubleshooting

- ESM plugin error (require vs ESM):
  - If you see errors like “resolved to an ESM file … cannot be loaded by require”, remove ESM-only imports from `vite.renderer.config.ts` and rely on PostCSS for Tailwind.
- 500 loading `index.css`:
  - Install `@tailwindcss/postcss` and use it in `postcss.config.cjs`.
- Electron dev security warning (CSP):
  - This warning appears in development; it won’t show in packaged builds.
- Windows GPU/net cache errors:
  - Common in dev sandboxes; usually harmless and don’t affect functionality.

